RDS- Relational Database Service - It is fully Amazon owned/managed Database service.
In order to build a database in cloud, we are doing this. MySQL, MariaDB, Oracle,PostgreSQL, Aurora(Amazon's db).

RDS Benefits:-
Amazon managed service.
Automatic provisioning
AWS Backup service - point-in-time restore
Monitoring RDS from Dashboard
MultiAZ - Disaster Recovery.(Amazon recommended)
Maintenance timing
scaling capability - vertical scaling and Horizontal scaling

I.Q: RDS instance depends on **Linux OS**

AWS Default Automated snapshots --> this can be taken at specific time everyday.
AWS Backup service - Here, Point-in-time option keeps restoring every changes from time to time which saves us from data loss even when Db is crashed accidentally.
